{"id":34770,"title":"Aortic dissection associated with penetration of a spinal pedicle screw: a case report and review of the literature.","abstract":"A 30-year-old male underwent a corrective posterior instrumented spinal fusion for scoliosis. Six years later, he was found to have an aortic dissection after aortic penetration of a spinal pedicle screw. We review the literature, including diagnostic modalities, and treatment decision-making for this unusual complication.","date":"2014-04-25","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24707982","annotations":[{"name":"Scoliosis","weight":0.825798,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scoliosis"},{"name":"Aortic dissection","weight":0.664554,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aortic_dissection"},{"name":"Vertebral column","weight":0.556912,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebral_column"},{"name":"Aorta","weight":0.532642,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aorta"},{"name":"Spinal fusion","weight":0.435303,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spinal_fusion"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.377256,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.260731,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Dissection","weight":0.206031,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dissection"},{"name":"Literature","weight":0.148691,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literature"},{"name":"Posterior (anatomy)","weight":0.108017,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posterior_(anatomy)"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Male","weight":0.0532834,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Male"},{"name":"Pedicle of vertebral arch","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":